Class JDialogColumns

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.RootPaneContainer, javax.swing.WindowConstants

    public class JDialogColumns
extends JDialogSession
    A dialog to selected columns (fields) either to set the visible columns in a JTableRecord or to set an order to sort it. Usage:
    • Instantiate the dialog.
    • Set the master record.
    • Optionally set the list of available field aliases.
    • Request the order or the list of selected fields. Note that the selected request sets the JPanelColumns.Mode.
    Author:
    Miquel Sas
